# Black Eagle Group Website - Cursor Rules

## Project Structure
This is a multi-directory project with the main React application in `BlackEagleGroup.React/`.

## Dependency Management

### CRITICAL: Always use the correct directory for package management
- The React app lives in `BlackEagleGroup.React/` - ALL npm/bun commands must run from this directory
- Before running `bun install`, `bun add`, `npm install`, or similar commands, ALWAYS `cd` to `BlackEagleGroup.React/` first
- Use absolute paths when uncertain: `cd "C:\Users\Theo\Desktop\Projects\Websites\Black Eagle Group\BlackEagleGroup.React"`

### Before adding new imports
1. Check if the package exists in `BlackEagleGroup.React/package.json`
2. If not, install it BEFORE adding the import: `cd BlackEagleGroup.React; bun add <package-name>`
3. Verify installation by checking `BlackEagleGroup.React/node_modules/<package-name>` exists

### After modifying package.json manually
- Always run `bun install` in `BlackEagleGroup.React/` to sync node_modules

## PowerShell Compatibility
- Use `;` instead of `&&` to chain commands (PowerShell doesn't support `&&`)
- Example: `cd BlackEagleGroup.React; bun dev` NOT `cd BlackEagleGroup.React && bun dev`

## Code Quality

### CRITICAL: Always add imports when using functions/modules
- When using a function, component, or utility from another file, ALWAYS add the corresponding import statement
- Before using any function (e.g., `initScrollAnimations()`), verify it's imported at the top of the file
- Check existing usage patterns in similar files (e.g., look at `Home.jsx` when modifying `About.jsx`)
- Common project utilities to import:
  - `import { initScrollAnimations } from '@/utils/scrollAnimations'`
  - `import AnimatedElement from '@/components/animations/AnimatedElement'`

## Development Server
- Dev server runs on `http://localhost:5173/`
- Start with: `cd BlackEagleGroup.React; bun dev`
- If import errors occur after adding dependencies, restart the dev server

## Key Directories
- `BlackEagleGroup.React/` - Main React application (Vite + React + TailwindCSS)
- `BlackEagleGroup.React/src/` - Source code
- `BlackEagleGroup.React/public/` - Static assets
- `agent-os/` - Project documentation and specs
- `public_html/` - Legacy static HTML site (reference only)
